text: Welp, it seems my iPhone Excess-to-the-Max is napping somewhere in ZhengZhao, courtesy @UPSHelp? It arrived in ZhengZhao 2 days ago and tracking now says "Scheduled delivery information is not available at this time." #overload? The estimate is gone!
RT @HappyFeetJam: My iPhone XS Max was supposed to come Friday @UPS reschedule my package to Today.... I’m at the door waiting.... #apple #…
@HappyFeetJam @UPS You figured it out, pirate. You figured this whole how-to-live thing out. Well done, sir, and I salute you!

Okay, @AppleSupport y @UPSHelp... I preordered my iPhone in the first minute of availability on the 14th and tracking stills shows the phone is hanging out in Zhengzhou, China -- since the 21st. Scheduled delivery says "information unavailable"...? What's going on?
Same here. @UPSHelp said it’s because of customs. @AppleSupport said to see if it shows up this week sometime. Mildly frustrating. https://t.co/pofBe7TFhh
@sbingner @UPS @Apple I love that a BOT replied to this. Yeesh.

@floridensis I can understand your concern as your package has not been placed in transit. Please continue to track your package online at https://t.co/1ruUS3ncQ2 for updates. Your online tracking will be updated once we have any movement on the package. ^TT
@UPSHelp Thanks for the generic, automated response, @UPSHelp! You make a boy feel super special and valued! Maybe now you can move my phone out of China?

@floridensis Our records show that the package was shipped on 09/21/18. China was on Holiday from 09/22/18-09/24/18. The package is in transit and the delivery date will update soon. Please continue to track the package at https://t.co/B99xu461QJ for updated info. ^SB

@UPSHelp Earlier, I was told by UPS (via online support) that the package hadn’t cleared customs and that I should contact the sender, Apple - not UPS. Seems like the holiday thing might have been useful information to share earlier?
